    <chapter>
        <header>Search results page</header>
        <section help-key="search-results-1">
            <header>Result page</header>
            <content>
                <p>After submitting a search query, the search results are displayed.
                   The search results page is divided into two areas.
                   On the right you will find the main results list, to the left of this are further
                   filtering and restriction options.
                   The main results list is sorted by relevance.
                   The top entry has the highest relevance for the search query.</p>
                <p>A search result consists of a title that links to the metadata entry,
                   a short description and further information such as contact persons,
                   references and terms of use.
                   If a digital map is deposited with a catalog entry, you can view the map
                   directly in the <a href="?hkey=maps-1">map viewer</a> using the <b>open map view</b> button.
                   The <b>XML</b> button provides the ISO representation of the hit,
                   provided that it can be submitted in accordance with CSW.</p>
            </content>
        </section>
    </chapter>
    <chapter>
        <header>Catalog</header>
        <section help-key="search-catalog-1">
            <header>Catalog</header>
            <content>
                <p>Search the structure of the BASt metadata catalog.
                   The structure is hierarchical and can be expanded or collapsed by clicking on "+"/"-".
                   The information displayed is referred to as <b>Objects</b>.
                   The relevant contact persons are listed in the <b>Addresses</b>
                   area as additional information.
                   Clicking on an object or address displays detailed information.</p>
            </content>
        </section>
    </chapter>
    <chapter>
        <header>Maps</header>
        <section help-key="maps-1">
            <header>Overview</header>
             <content>
                <p>With the map viewer you can view a variety of maps and work on them.</p>
                <p>Its functionality includes:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        layer-centered display of maps with direct preview
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        structured offering of maps and adding external maps
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        search for maps directly on embedded maps or in the search area of the BASt metadata catalog
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        drawing and measuring on the map
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        comparison functionality between layers (slider fades in or out)
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        saving and sharing maps e.g. via QR code
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        comprehensive printing functionality
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </content>
        </section>
        <section help-key="maps-2">
            <header>Coordinates display</header>
            <content>
                <p>The coordinates of the cursor in the selected coordinate system are displayed directly
                below the main map.</p>
                <p>By right-clicking on a point in the map, further information is displayed in an
                additional window.</p>
            </content>
        </section>
    </chapter>
    <chapter>
        <header>Categories</header>
        <section help-key="search-category-1">
            <header>Search the portal by categories</header>
            <content>
                <p>On the home page, you can search for categories in the lower area.
                   By selecting a category, all existing hits in the selected category are displayed
                   as result types on the search results page.</p>
            </content>
        </section>
